\subsection{Residue field}
\begin{definition}\label{lf.residue_field}
\uses{lf.maximal_ideal,lf.ring_of_integers}
The **residue field** of a nonarchimedean local field is the quotient of its {{KNOWL('lf.ring_of_integers', 'ring of integers')}} by its unique {{KNOWL('lf.maximal_ideal', 'maximal ideal')}}.

The residue field is finite and its characteristic $p$ is the **residue field characteristic**.  Finite extensions of $\Q_p$ have residue field characteristic $p$.
\end{definition}


